wiki.summary: "Supernova" is a song recorded by the South Korean girl group aespa. It was released on May 13, 2024, by SM Entertainment as a pre-release single from their debut full-length studio album, "Armageddon". The song addresses themes of explosive growth and overwhelming power, metaphorically likening the group's impact on the music industry to that of a supernova. wiki.content: "Supernova" is a song recorded by the South Korean girl group aespa. It was released on May 13, 2024, by SM Entertainment as a pre-release single from their debut full-length studio album, "Armageddon". The song addresses themes of explosive growth and overwhelming power, metaphorically likening the group's impact on the music industry to that of a supernova. Featuring a blend of innovative electronic elements and powerful vocals, "Supernova" received critical acclaim for its production quality and lyrical depth, further establishing aespa as a leading force in the K-pop genre.
